<TITLE> 3 bombs, one on timer, retrieved in Jessore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Jessore, Dec 22 (bdnews24.com)Police retrieved a powerful bomb on a timer and two hand bombs in Jessore on Monday; explosives experts have been called in to defuse them, police guarding the spot said. "We were tipped off Monday morning about three bombs being cached somewhere behind the cowshed of a man named 'Tota', known to be the son of Islam Ghani, in Chatkapota village, Sarsha Upazila," said Sarsha police sub-inspector Iqbal Hossain. Acting upon the intelligence, police went to the village and discovered the one large bomb with a timer attached and two smaller bombs, said the sub-inspector. "Police cordoned off the spot and informed Bangladesh Army bomb experts to intervene and defuse the bombs." In a separate incident, RAB-6 troopers from Jessore retrieved 10 kgs of explosives after raidingthe house of a man named 'Nasir' in Kalinia village and. Nasir is known to be the son of Abdur Rouf also of the village. Police are investigating whether these explosives were intended for carrying out "sabotage activities", while intelligence personnel have already begun probing the matter at the field level, officials said. bdne
